      <h2 id="viz1">Visualization 1</h2>

      <svg width="100%" height="400" style="background-color: whitesmoke; border: 1px solid black;">
      </svg>

      <h3>Interpretation</h3>

      <p>
        Provide a brief discussion of how to interpret this visualization. Legends provided with the visualization can be self-explanatory, keep it short.
     By combining the location of deaths related to cholera with locations of the water pumps, the map is able to show us that the majority were clustered around public water pump.
the visualization show clearly a connection between location of water pump and the cluster of deaths (people was contaminated by public water).
      </p>

      <h3>Discussion</h3>

      <p>
        Provide a brief discussion of the key findings of the visualization, any challenges encountered creating the visualization etc.
     I was pretty impressed about the power of folium module.
The main challenge is to start using it, Once it's done, it becomes quickly a user friendly package with a really interesting items to visualize a map.
      
      </p>

      <h3>Sources</h3>

      <p>
        Provide sources for the dataset, any code used, and design inspirations here. Dishonesty will result in a 0 for the assignment or the <strong>entire course</strong>.
      Robin Wilsonâ€™s blog
      OpenstreetMap
      Datacamp
        Code :
 import folium
 import pandas as pd

deaths=pd.read_csv('/Users/otb/Desktop/deaths.csv')
deaths
# Rename your columns

newcols = {
    'Death': 'death_count',
    'X coordinate': 'x_latitude', 
    'Y coordinate': 'y_longitude' 
    }

deaths.rename(columns=newcols, inplace=True)

locations = deaths[['x_latitude', 'y_longitude']]
deaths_list = locations.values.tolist()
deaths_list 
map = folium.Map(location=[51.5132119,-0.13666], tiles='Stamen Toner', zoom_start=18)
for point in range(0, len(deaths_list)):
    folium.CircleMarker(deaths_list[point], radius=18, color='red', fill=True, fill_color='red', opacity = 0.4).add_to(map)
map
        
# Import the data
pumps = pd.read_csv('/Users/otb/Desktop/pumps.csv')

# Subset the DataFrame 
locations_pumps = pumps[['X coordinate', 'Y coordinate']]

# Transform the DataFrame to list of lists 
pumps_list = locations_pumps.values.tolist()

# Create a for loop (use previous map)
map1 = map
for point in range(0, len(pumps_list)):
    folium.Marker(pumps_list[point], popup=pumps['Pump Name'][point]).add_to(map1)
map1

#output Visualization on the link
        
      </p>
